json.name: Mihir Shukla
json.position: Co-Founder, CEO and Chairman at Automation Anywhere
json.description:
Co-Founder, CEO and Chairman at Automation Anywhere · Mihir Shukla is co-founder, Chairman and CEO of Automation Anywhere, a global leader in Agentic Process Automation and AI solutions for the enterprise.

Mihir co-founded Automation Anywhere in 2003. Through his leadership, the company’s vision is to fuel the future of work by unleashing human potential through an Autonomous Enterprise where up to 80% of work is fully automated or AI-assisted, enabling people to focus on what matters most. Alongside rapid growth and profitability, Automation Anywhere has received numerous awards for its groundbreaking technology and customer-first approach, including being named in Forbes as one of the Seven Wonders of AI; frequent market leadership positions from top analysts such as Gartner and Forrester; annual listings on the Forbes Cloud 100 list; and numerous accolades for Automation Anywhere's positive culture, including being recognized as a Great Place to Work and featured in Newsweek’s America’s Top 200

json.name: Aayush Ghosh Choudhury
json.description:
Co-Founder/CEO at Scrut Automation (scrut.io) · What if you could cut through the noise of security tools, customer questionnaires, and compliance frameworks?

How much better could you manage your risk?

In 2023, it’s nearly impossible to run a business without:
- Answering customer security questions or agreeing to contractual provisions.
- Meeting industry and regulatory standards for data protection.
- Dealing with a constant stream of attacks against your network.

These things all require time and attention, when you have dozens of other pressing needs. Like delivering value to your customers and running your business.

- During your sales cycle, how frequently do you find yourself answering bespoke questionnaires that ask the same questions in many different ways?

- Do you have to address multiple compliance frameworks and audit processes, all with slightly different requirements and controls?
